commit.message: Tweak for older sqlites

Add a new API, .converter(), for specifying a value conversion.

This patch fixes #2248.

Peewee has a few heuristics for finding a conversion to apply to a
row value pulled off the cursor, but when referencing subquery columns
or other dynamically-defined columns, it may be useful to specify this
conversion explicitly.

Support specifying index-type with MySQL.

The USING block goes before the indexed relation in MySQL, whereas with
Postgres it goes after. This extends the sql generation of the Index
type to support both modes.

Fixes #2242

Include "\" in list of characters to escape in contains() / etc.

Fixes #2233.

Escape wildcards in contains(), startswith() and endswith().
